
Recap



Topics:

    Window vs Document

      window:
        It is the main javascript object root, global object in a browser. 
        window object represents an open window in a browser.

      Document:

        document is an object inside window

        when an HTML document is loaded into a web browser, it becomes a document object.
        document object is the root node of the HTML document

        window.document or just document is the main object of the potentially 
        visible (or better yet: rendered) document object model/DOM.

        Commonly used window until functions
          
          alert, confirm, prompt,
          alert --> a simple alert for the user
          confirm --> confirm prompts the user to cancenl or ok
              return true or false
          prompt ---> Gets an input from the user
            return input-value-from-user

          localStorage, sessionStorage
          https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/localStorage

          setTimeout, 
            Do an action after specified amount of time
            clearTimeout ---> clears setTimeout

          setInterval, 
            do an action on a specified intervals
           clearInterval ---> clears setInterval
        
        Reference: https://www.w3schools.com/jsref/obj_window.asp


